notes.text: An update for lldpad is now available for Red Hat Enterprise Linux 7.
notes.title: Topic

notes.text:
The lldpad packages provide the Linux user space daemon and configuration tool for Intel's Link Layer Discovery Protocol (LLDP) Agent with Enhanced Ethernet support.

For detailed information on changes in this release, see the Red Hat Enterprise Linux 7.7 Release Notes linked from the References section.

Users of lldpad are advised to upgrade to these updated packages.

acknowledgments.summary: This issue was discovered by Red Hat.

notes.text: lldptool can print a raw, unsanitized attacker controlled buffer when mngAddr information is displayed. This may allow an attacker to inject shell control characters into the buffer and impact the behavior of the terminal.
notes.title: Vulnerability description
